cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a set of novel quality criteria for evaluating deep models for single-image depth estimation. The focus is on specific characteristics of depth maps such as edge and planar region preservation, depth consistency, and absolute distance accuracy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the authors used a DSLR camera and a laser scanner to acquire high-resolution images and highly accurate depth maps, indicating that robotics (cs.RO) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) could be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which could be of interest to the graphics (cs.GR) community.
